  "text": "The impact of each exposure on asthma phenotypes was estimated by the adjusted Population Attributable Risk (aPAR), the fraction of the total disease experienced in the population that would not have occurred if the effect associated with the risk factor of interest was absent [CITATION_1] . The aPARs were calculated with the formula provided by Bruzzi [CITATION_2] :",
